      "message": "Just brainstorming: Receiver could have a method like\nNewStream(stepId string, streamName string) (io.Writer, error)\n\nUse something like io.MultiWriter to write to all Receivers (probably ignore all errors though).\n\nThen Step can use NewStream(s.Id, \"stdout\") and use that as exec.Command.Stdout.\n\nDebugReceiver could just return exec.WriteInfoLog / WriteErrorLog for NewStream; ReportReceiver would probably use bytes.Buffer, possibly with LimitWriter.\n\n(Most likely we would only have streams named \"stdout\" and \"stderr\", but I\u0027m thinking it might be nice e.g. for dm to have a \"verbose\" stream in addition to stderr and stdout.)",
